Definition: doing as one pleases or chooses

Definition: a general category of things; used in the expression `in the way of'
Examples: they didn't have much in the way of clothing.

Definition: a portion of something divided into shares
Examples: they split the loot three ways.

Definition: be the winner in a contest or competition; be victorious
Examples: He won the Gold Medal in skating.  Our home team won.  Win the game.

Definition: win something through one's efforts
Examples: I acquired a passing knowledge of Chinese.  Gain an understanding of international finance.

Definition: obtain advantages, such as points, etc.
Examples: The home team was gaining ground.  After defeating the Knicks, the Blazers pulled ahead of the Lakers in the battle for the number-one playoff berth in the Western Conference.
WordNetSynonyms: gain#5 (gain%2:33:00::), advance#6 (advance%2:33:00::), win#3 (win%2:33:01::), pull ahead#1 (pull_ahead%2:33:00::), make headway#1 (make_headway%2:33:00::), get ahead#1 (get_ahead%2:33:00::), gain ground#1 (gain_ground%2:33:00::)

Definition: attain success or reach a desired goal
Examples: The enterprise succeeded.  We succeeded in getting tickets to the show.  she struggled to overcome her handicap and won.
WordNetSynonyms: succeed#1 (succeed%2:41:00::), win#4 (win%2:41:04::), come through#4 (come_through%2:41:00::), bring home the bacon#1 (bring_home_the_bacon%2:41:00::), deliver the goods#1 (deliver_the_goods%2:41:00::)

Definition: a framework of wood or metal that contains a glass windowpane and is built into a wall or roof to admit light or air
a transparent opening in a vehicle that allow vision out of the sides or back; usually is capable of being opened
a transparent panel (as of an envelope) inserted in an otherwise opaque material
an opening that resembles a window in appearance or function
Examples: he could see them through a window in the trees.

Definition: the time period that is considered best for starting or finishing something
Examples: the expanded window will give us time to catch the thieves.  they had a window of less than an hour when an attack would have succeeded.

Definition: a pane of glass in a window
Examples: the ball shattered the window.

Definition: an opening in a wall or screen that admits light and air and through which customers can be served
Examples: he stuck his head in the window.

Definition: (computer science) a rectangular part of a computer screen that contains a display different from the rest of the screen
activity directed toward making or doing something
Examples: she checked several points needing further work.

Definition: a product produced or accomplished through the effort or activity or agency of a person or thing
Examples: it is not regarded as one of his more memorable works.  the symphony was hailed as an ingenious work.  he was indebted to the pioneering work of John Dewey.  the work of an active imagination.  erosion is the work of wind or water over time.

Definition: the occupation for which you are paid
Examples: he is looking for employment.  a lot of people are out of work.

Definition: applying the mind to learning and understanding a subject (especially by reading)
Examples: mastering a second language requires a lot of work.  no schools offer graduate study in interior design.

Definition: (physics) a manifestation of energy; the transfer of energy from one physical system to another expressed as the product of a force and the distance through which it moves a body in the direction of that force
Examples: work equals force times distance.

Definition: a place where work is done
Examples: he arrived at work early today.

Definition: the total output of a writer or artist (or a substantial part of it)
Examples: he studied the entire Wagnerian oeuvre.  Picasso's work can be divided into periods.
